dji.sdk.api.Camera

Class DJICamera

  • java.lang.Object
    • dji.sdk.api.DJIObject
      • dji.sdk.api.Camera.DJICamera
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    DJIInspireCamera, DJIPhantomCamera

    public class DJICamera
extends DJIObject

    DJI Camera Base Class

    DJICamera is a base class for the camera of DJI drone. All the functions in DJICamera is designed for getting & setting camera parameters, taking photos, recording videos, and receiving media data in SDcard.

    You could use this class to modify the parameter settings of photos and recordings so that they could satisfy your requirements. For example, if you want to adjust the size of photo you take, setCameraPhotoSize may help you to do that. With the help of the predefined enums, you could directly set up the parameters.
    Version:
    V2.1.0
    Author:
    DJI Software

        Returns:
